Package com.organism

Class Organism

java.lang.Object
com.organism.Organism
public class Organism extends Object
This class is used to make an organism with information in attributes such as: clade names, genus & species, defining features, and measurements. Organism class to create organism object with attributes, getters and setters, a constructor, and a toString() method.

    • Organism

      public Organism(String id, String cladeName, String genusSpecies, int lifespanEstimate, String lifespanUnit, String definitiveFeatures, float averageLength, String lengthUnit)
      Constructor for a new Organism with all required attributes.
      Parameters:
      id - organism ID/primary key
      cladeName - scientific clade/group name
      genusSpecies - genus and species name
      lifespanEstimate - estimated lifespan of organism
      lifespanUnit - measurement unit for lifespan (years, minutes)
      definitiveFeatures - notable physical or behavioral features of the organism
      averageLength - average length value
      lengthUnit - unit for the average length (cm, m, or mm)
